        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We tested <span class="accent">10 tools</span> against five HVAC-specific criteria.</h2>
      <p>HVAC search volume swings 300–400% between summer AC and winter heating. Most HVAC companies serve 20–50 mile areas with multiple cities. We measured every tool against these two defining challenges.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 HVAC-specific benchmarks.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Same scorecard across all 10 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Seasonal content</h4>
              <p>Can the tool produce content aligned with seasonal demand shifts? HVAC search volume swings 300–400% between summer AC and winter heating.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Service area coverage</h4>
              <p>Does it track or target rankings across wide geographic zones? Most HVAC companies serve 20–50+ mile areas with multiple cities.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>GBP management</h4>
              <p>Can it create, schedule, or optimize Google Business Profile content? "AC repair near me" queries pull from the local pack.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content creation</h4>
              <p>Does it produce blog articles, GBP posts, or other content? Content creation moves rankings; tracking only measures them.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Price-to-value</h4>
              <p>What does an HVAC business actually get per dollar? Most HVAC companies spend marketing budgets on trucks and technicians, not agencies.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Content creation is the gap. Tracking tools are everywhere.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Key findings across the field.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>9 of 10 tools track but don't create</h4>
              <p>Only theStacc produces HVAC content. Every other tool on this list measures rankings without improving them through content.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Seasonal targeting is nearly unsupported</h4>
              <p>No tool automatically shifts content strategy from AC to heating seasonally — except theStacc, which handles seasonal keyword targeting as part of its automated content pipeline.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
