      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, one-paragraph verdict, pros, and one honest con.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · $99/MO BLOG · $49/MO LOCAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best for automated HVAC blog content and GBP posts</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For any HVAC company that wants to publish seasonal content consistently without hiring a writer or agency.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">theStacc publishes 30 blog articles monthly targeting HVAC-specific keywords and seasonal demand — AC content in spring, heating content in fall. It also publishes 30 GBP posts monthly. No writing, editing, or uploading required. At $99/month for 30 articles, that's roughly $3.30 per article. No other tool on this list creates content instead of just tracking it.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Seasonal HVAC keyword targeting — automatic</h4>
              <p>Shifts content focus between AC and heating content based on the time of year. Start publishing AC content in March; you're positioned to rank by June.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>30 blog articles + 30 GBP posts per month</h4>
              <p>The only tool in this category that actually creates content rather than measuring it. $3.30 per article is 1/40th the cost of a freelancer.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Price: $49 local / $99 blog / ~$126 bundle</h4>
              <p>Cancel anytime. Content stays on your site forever. No setup fees, no change orders, no long-term contracts.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
