        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Should I focus on "near me" keywords or city-specific keywords?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Both. "AC repair near me" captures high-intent mobile searchers. "HVAC [city name]" captures people searching with specific locations. Your GBP optimization handles the "near me" searches. Your blog content targets city-specific long-tail keywords like "furnace replacement cost [city]."</div>
